	<div class="expert-content-text">
		<p>To see all Cocktails articles, <a href="http://cocktails.about.com/" data-component="contentBioPage" data-source="channelhomepage" data-type="site.displayName" data-ordinal="1" itemprop="url">click here</a>.</p>
		<p><p>Colleen Graham is a mixologist and writer with a passion for creating and sharing great cocktails and mixed drinks that enrich the everyday drinking experience.</p>

<p>Follow me on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ColleensDrinkStudio" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/cocktailsguide" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">Twitter</a>, <a href="https://plus.google.com/+ColleenGraham/posts" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">Google+</a>, <a href="http://www.pinterest.com/cocktailsguide/" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">Pinterest</a>, and <a href="http://instagram.com/scdesignstudios/" zT="-o1/XJ" target="_blank">Instagram</a>.</p></p>
		<h5>Experience</h5>
		<p><p>Colleen joined About.com in 2006 as the Cocktails Expert and has since researched and reported on a variety of aspects in the art and practice of creating fine drinks. This experience has allowed Colleen to rediscover <a href="/od/cocktailrecipes/a/classic_cktls.htm">classic cocktails</a> and their history, create and try new, more culinary drinks, explore and review the array of distilled spirits available, and go behind the scenes with the people of today's hospitality and liquor industries.</p>

<p>Colleen is also a cocktail consultant, creating themed cocktail menus and individual drink recipes for a variety of clients. She is a regular drink columnist for Maximum Yield's HydroLife and in 2015 launched the website <a href="http://www.scdrinkstudio.com/" zT="-o1/XJ" target="_blank">SCDrinkStudio.com</a>, which focuses on non-alcoholic beverages. In addition to writing and consulting, Colleen owns and operates a commercial and fine art studio with her husband, Shannon, and beverage photography just happens to be one of their specialties.</p>

<h3>Colleen's Books</h3>

<p>In 2012, Colleen's first book was published. <a href="http://scgrahamfoto.com/2012/03/hola-tequila-book-release-in-march/" zT="-o1/XJ" target="_blank"><em>&iexcl;Hola Tequila!</em></a> is a celebration of tequila and includes 90 cocktail and shooter recipes, tequila history, production, and tips for setting up a tequila-centered bar.</p>

<p><a href="http://erclk.about.com/?zi=7/3Hu9" zT="-o1/XJ" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Compare Prices on <em>&iexcl;Hola Tequila!</em></a></p></p>
			<h5>Colleen Graham</h5>
			<p><p>I invite you to join me in learning the art of mixing cocktails and experimenting with new and interesting flavors. The diversity in tastes and styles of cocktails is so vast that it is a never-ending pursuit and this site is designed to help everyone along this path because I firmly believe that everyone deserves a great drink.</p>

<p>Whether you are building a home bar to entertain friends and family, are looking to try something new at your favorite lounge, or are curious about a particular drink that you have heard of, you will find the information you need here. I&#39;ll also share my thoughts on a variety of distilled spirits to help you choose a brand that fits your particular taste and give you some ideas for hosting parties and making your cocktails look and taste great.</p>

<p>I welcome any recipes, suggestions, and requests via email: drinkstudio@scgrahamphoto.com.</p>

<p><em>For marketing representatives:</em><br />
I am happy to receive information and review distilled spirits, tools, books, and other materials related to cocktails, drinks, and bartending. However, I do ask that you email me prior to sending any unsolicited material. It will save both of us time and energy. Thank you.</p></p>
	</div>

